Give in--------------------------------------------------
Imagine:---
Imagine a concentric office building with only one employee on each circle. Tasks rushes in in the form of football. First the employee at out-most circle tries to catch it otherwise he gives in, similar is the case of other employees.
Hindi Meaning:---
chod dena (because of outer pressure)
If you give in, you admit that you are defeated or that you cannot do something.
If you give in, you agree to do something that you do not want to do.
Sentences:---
I pressed my parents until they finally gave in and bought me a bike.
Lexicon!:---
Check Out:---
